        <h3 class="center ProductReview-title" tabindex="">
             
                Waterpik Powerpulse - Best Handheld Shower Head
             
        </h3>
    

    
      <div class="RichTextBody body-2">
          <ps-toggler data-toggle="review" class="ToggleText " itemprop="description" data-fade-out="true">
    
        <div data-toggle-content
            data-size="large"
            class="ToggleText-content body-1">
            <p>The Waterpik Powerpulse is our favorite handheld showerhead because it features massage technology that provides up to two times the massage force of other showerheads. The flexible, 5-foot-long hose makes it easy to reach any part of your body to help relieve muscle tension and promote relaxation. By quickly detaching it from its base, you can have a powerful and refreshing massage experience you can’t get with the other handheld showerheads on our list.</p>

<div class="row ProductReview-injectedProsCons">
    
        <ul class="ProductReview-pros">
            
                <li>
                        <span>
                            <svg class="plus-circle-icon">
                                <use xlink:href="#plus-circle"></use>
                            </svg>
                        </span>
                    <span>Easy to install</span>
                </li>
            
                <li>
                        <span>
                            <svg class="plus-circle-icon">
                                <use xlink:href="#plus-circle"></use>
                            </svg>
                        </span>
                    <span>Nine spray modes</span>
                </li>
            
                <li>
                        <span>
                            <svg class="plus-circle-icon">
                                <use xlink:href="#plus-circle"></use>
                            </svg>
                        </span>
                    <span>Anti-clog feature</span>
                </li>
            
        </ul>
    
    
    <ul class="ProductReview-cons">
        
            <li>
                    <span>
                        <svg class="minus-circle-icon">
                            <use xlink:href="#minus-circle"></use>
                        </svg>
                    </span>
                <span>Certain spray settings may be too weak for some people</span>
            </li>
        
            <li>
                    <span>
                        <svg class="minus-circle-icon">
                            <use xlink:href="#minus-circle"></use>
                        </svg>
                    </span>
                <span>High-pressure settings may be too intense for some users</span>
            </li>
        
            <li>
                    <span>
                        <svg class="minus-circle-icon">
                            <use xlink:href="#minus-circle"></use>
                        </svg>
                    </span>
                <span>The complex design can make it difficult to clean</span>
            </li>
        
    </ul>
    
</div>

<p>This showerhead has nine spray modes, letting you customize your shower experience to your body’s needs. These modes include full-body spray, power pulse massage, power mist, circular massage, and more. Whether you need a deep massage or gentle mist, the Waterpik Powerpulse can pretty much do it all. It’s also made from high-quality materials such as durable, high-grade plastic and stainless steel to ensure you have a superior shower for many years to come.</p><p>The Waterpik Powerpulse is WaterSense certified, which means it meets EPA criteria for water efficiency and can help you save water and money on your water bill. </p><p><b>Water usage:</b> 1.8 gallons per minute flow rate<br><b>Water coverage:</b> Adequate water coverage<br><b>Variable settings:</b> 9 settings <br><b>Assembly/installation:</b> Wall-mounted<br><b>Looks and options:</b> Available in Chrome or Brushed Nickel</p><p><b>Price:</b> $</p>
